[30;1m39 | [0m[35mcount (with the default TextInputFormat). The key/value stream emitted[0m

[30;1m290 | [0m[35m        Reporting progress is strictly necessary only when using a Python[0m
[30;1m291 | [0m[35m        record writer, because sending an output key/value pair is an implicit[0m
[30;1m292 | [0m[35m        progress report. To take advantage of this, however, we would be[0m
[30;1m293 | [0m[35m        forced to flush the uplink stream at every output, and that would be[0m
[30;1m294 | [0m[35m        too costly. Rather than add a specific timer for this, we just call[0m
[30;1m295 | [0m[35m        progress unconditionally and piggyback on its timer instead. Note that[0m
[30;1m296 | [0m[35m        when a combiner is caching there is no actual output, so in that case[0m
